WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:41.030 --> 00:46.030
Subtitles by explosiveskull

00:47.596 --> 00:49.662
- [girl] Beth, is it on?
- [Beth] We're rolling.

00:49.664 --> 00:51.298
[girl] Places, guys.
This one's for real.

00:51.300 --> 00:56.769
"For centuries, the dark hand of Narash has
been spreading across the borderlands,

00:56.771 --> 00:59.573
ruling with blood
and necromancy.

00:59.575 --> 01:04.810
Are you the chosen one to challenge
him, to crush his bones into dust,

01:04.812 --> 01:07.747
and pry out his innards
with the tip of your sword?"

01:07.749 --> 01:09.548
- [Meg] Beth, film me.
- [hisses]

01:09.550 --> 01:11.817
[Beth] Meg, you look like a boy.
[giggles]

01:11.819 --> 01:14.554
- Yes! I am the...
- That's my part.

01:14.556 --> 01:16.555
I just wanted to make
sure you did it right.

01:16.557 --> 01:18.691
This is the pivotal point
for your character.

01:18.693 --> 01:20.659
- Just let me do it my way.
- But I'm the director.

01:20.661 --> 01:21.828
- [Beth] Hi, Amy.
- [giggles]

01:21.830 --> 01:24.563
- [Meg] Okay, fine.
- [Beth] Try it again.

01:24.565 --> 01:30.003
"I am the rightful paladin. Tell me my path,
Lord Gillian, I shall fulfill my prophecy."

01:30.005 --> 01:34.039
"You must travel beyond
the catacombs of Eryx,

01:34.041 --> 01:38.177
through the valley of Guell,
and climb the denizen steps

01:38.179 --> 01:41.114
where no human has dared
to venture."

01:41.116 --> 01:43.116
"Ever dared to venture, yet."

01:43.118 --> 01:48.554
Uh, it's more like:
"Ever dared to venture, yet!"

01:48.556 --> 01:50.090
In order to continue,

01:50.092 --> 01:52.591
you must offer
sacrifice to Rian,

01:52.593 --> 01:55.661
a dark fairy
of the Killian order.

01:55.663 --> 01:58.265
"You must bring me
the dragon scale relic

01:58.267 --> 01:59.599
of the forgotten droids."

01:59.601 --> 02:01.134
- [giggles]
- Druids!

02:01.136 --> 02:02.903
Whatever.

02:02.905 --> 02:05.739
- "Do you accept?"
- "I am not afraid."

02:05.741 --> 02:09.743
She turned and said farewell,
floating bravely forth,

02:09.745 --> 02:13.515
on her long, unknown journey,
far away.

02:16.585 --> 02:18.718
- End book one.
- [girls clapping]

02:18.720 --> 02:20.754
[Beth] Hey, Jo,
do the epilogue!

02:20.756 --> 02:22.622
But we've heard it
a million times!

02:22.624 --> 02:24.660
It's my favorite part.

02:25.727 --> 02:27.663
The people have spoken.

02:28.329 --> 02:30.162
[sighs]

02:30.164 --> 02:34.333
[Jo] It is not enough for the brave
heroine to desire greatness.

02:34.335 --> 02:40.040
No, even the lowliest serf in the
kingdom may desire greatness.

02:40.042 --> 02:43.944
For our heroine to succeed,
she must demand greatness.

02:43.946 --> 02:45.979
To snatch it
from the powers that be

02:45.981 --> 02:48.948
and wave it over the parapet
for all to see.

02:48.950 --> 02:51.785
To prove
that she is their queen,

02:51.787 --> 02:56.926
and the magnificent rightful
heir to her birthright.

02:58.060 --> 02:59.529
[sighs]

03:00.628 --> 03:03.997
Uh, well,
thank you, Josephine.

03:03.999 --> 03:04.932
Oh, it's just Jo.

03:04.934 --> 03:08.100
You certainly gave us
an entertaining read.

03:08.102 --> 03:09.668
- [chuckles]
- [scoffs]

03:09.670 --> 03:12.805
Uh, listen,
it's not my taste per se,

03:12.807 --> 03:15.909
but I could see how it
could appeal to others.

03:15.911 --> 03:20.613
- What are you going for? Young adult fantasy?
- Uh, no.

03:20.615 --> 03:23.083
It can't be Y.A.
There's no love story.

03:23.085 --> 03:25.618
- It's not a love story.
- Then it's definitely a pass for me.

03:25.620 --> 03:28.755
- [Clarkson] Yeah, it's a pass for me as well.
- [Henry] Me too, sweetie.

03:28.757 --> 03:33.093
You have a very creative mind.

03:33.095 --> 03:37.297
But, there's something
missing in the authenticity.

03:37.299 --> 03:38.765
I can't hear your voice.

03:38.767 --> 03:39.965
It's not about me!

03:39.967 --> 03:42.334
All the same,
it's still gonna be a pass.

03:42.336 --> 03:43.172
Professor?

03:47.008 --> 03:49.242
Yeah, it's a pass
from me as well.

03:49.244 --> 03:50.343
Thanks.

03:50.345 --> 03:52.678
No, thank you.

03:52.680 --> 03:54.947
Really I...

03:54.949 --> 03:58.851
I appreciate you judging
my artistic aptitude

03:58.853 --> 04:02.791
on three pages
of my 400-page novel.

04:05.661 --> 04:06.862
Thank you.

04:10.132 --> 04:13.333
[rhythmic tapping]

04:13.335 --> 04:16.136
[man singing gospel]
<i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>

04:16.137 --> 04:19.204
- <i>♪ Lord can you give me ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>

04:19.207 --> 04:21.975
- <i>♪ A little bit of grace ♪</i>
- [sighs]

04:21.976 --> 04:25.145
- <i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Oh, can you hear me? ♪</i>

04:25.147 --> 04:28.213
<i>♪ It's been one of those days ♪</i>

04:28.215 --> 04:34.720
- <i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>
- <i>♪ So I'll be waiting Down by the riverbanks ♪</i>

04:34.722 --> 04:39.895
- <i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>
- <i>♪ You know I'll be praying So please don't delay ♪</i>

04:41.162 --> 04:45.634
- <i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Oh, please don't delay ♪</i>

04:49.071 --> 04:50.840
[sighs]

05:03.285 --> 05:05.220
[sighs]

05:08.457 --> 05:11.057
Hurry up!
The lava's rising.

05:11.059 --> 05:13.259
[woman] Is there any way you could
give me a one-time extension?

05:13.261 --> 05:16.129
- I promise, it won't happen again.
- My earring!

05:16.131 --> 05:19.499
Leave it! No! She just
spontaneously combusted!

05:19.501 --> 05:21.234
- We have to move on.
- Oh, come on.

05:21.236 --> 05:22.335
Jo!

05:22.337 --> 05:23.936
She chose her fate.

05:23.938 --> 05:25.804
We are not
going without her.

05:25.806 --> 05:27.473
[woman] Is there any way
you could reverse the fee?

05:27.475 --> 05:29.475
- Apollyon!
- [woman] Yes?

05:29.477 --> 05:30.509
[girls calling]
Apollyon!

05:30.511 --> 05:32.345
[woman] I'm sorry.
Can you just hold?

05:32.347 --> 05:34.213
- [phone beeps]
- I am here!

05:34.215 --> 05:38.251
From whence come you,
and whither are you bound?

05:38.253 --> 05:41.121
We have traveled
from the city of desolation

05:41.123 --> 05:44.790
- through the fires of purgatory, fighting beasts of the night.
- [gasps]

05:44.792 --> 05:49.732
- We seek access to the city of Zion.
- Ooh. Hmm.

05:51.099 --> 05:52.968
You may release
your burdens.

05:55.302 --> 06:00.073
But you must each sacrifice
one valuable to the altar.

06:00.075 --> 06:04.244
But choose carefully.
Be not selfish!

06:04.246 --> 06:08.381
Whatever you select
must be of great value.

06:08.383 --> 06:10.986
Good. Yes.

06:13.020 --> 06:15.121
- Hair?
- It's valuable to me.

06:15.123 --> 06:15.858
Hmm.

06:17.992 --> 06:20.195
Your castles await you.

06:22.030 --> 06:23.997
- Go!
- [Jo] Except for Amy.

06:23.999 --> 06:24.898
- [phone beeps]
- Oh.

06:24.900 --> 06:26.999
- Hey!
- Oh. Ah.

06:27.001 --> 06:30.271
Hello? Thanks for holding.
I'm so sorry.

06:36.511 --> 06:37.477
Hey, let me in!

06:37.479 --> 06:38.912
- [knocking]
- No! You cheated!

06:38.914 --> 06:40.345
You don't deserve
to be in the castle!

06:40.347 --> 06:42.381
- Just let her in.
- [Jo] She has to play by the rules!

06:42.383 --> 06:43.516
- [Amy knocking]
- It's just a game.

06:43.518 --> 06:45.888
- Let me in!
- [Jo] It's not a game to me!

06:46.987 --> 06:48.955
- Let me in!
- Let her in.

06:48.957 --> 06:51.523
- [sighs]
- All my sisters are allowed in my castle.

06:51.525 --> 06:53.228
[Meg] Mine too.

06:56.097 --> 06:58.100
- Oh, my goodness.
- This is so cool.

06:59.167 --> 07:00.035
Mine's pink!

07:03.003 --> 07:04.970
"Welcome to your castles
in the air.

07:04.972 --> 07:07.109
Fill them wisely.
Love Marmee."

07:12.179 --> 07:13.412
[gasps]

07:13.414 --> 07:17.917
- Jo, what's in your castle?
- [Jo] Well, I want a lot of things.

07:17.919 --> 07:20.319
- I, Jo March...
- [older Jo] <i>I, Jo March...</i>

07:20.321 --> 07:25.290
I, Jo March... I'll get out of this
town and move to the big city.

07:25.292 --> 07:28.528
I, Jo March, will be a
very successful writer

07:28.530 --> 07:32.131
and will buy a big house in the
city so we can all live together.

07:32.133 --> 07:34.199
[Meg] I don't want to
live with you forever!

07:34.201 --> 07:36.869
I want to get married
and have kids and...

07:36.871 --> 07:40.907
And have a nanny,
and a maid, and... a butler!

07:40.909 --> 07:44.276
- [Jo] Amy, that's stupid.
- [Meg] Hey, you can't judge other people's castles.

07:44.278 --> 07:47.213
[Jo] Fine.
Then I change the rules of mine.

07:47.215 --> 07:49.448
Only Beth and I are
allowed in my castle.

07:49.450 --> 07:50.884
[Amy] Hey!

07:50.886 --> 07:54.254
I, Jo March, will be
a very successful writer,

07:54.256 --> 07:56.122
and will visit
every single country

07:56.124 --> 07:57.924
and eat out
every single meal.

07:57.926 --> 08:03.028
Oh, and I will see every play and
musical and opera ever written.

08:03.030 --> 08:04.564
Or will be written
ever.

08:04.566 --> 08:06.435
[Beth]
I think that's too long.

08:08.102 --> 08:13.208
I, Jo March, will be a very
successful writer and will...

08:14.376 --> 08:16.878
do
all the things.

08:18.946 --> 08:20.415
[Amy] My turn.

08:22.316 --> 08:27.953
I, Amy March, will be...
a rich and famous painter

08:27.955 --> 08:30.355
so I can...

08:30.357 --> 08:33.325
buy whatever I want
and go wherever I want.

08:33.327 --> 08:34.928
[Beth giggles]
Amy.

08:34.929 --> 08:38.996
I, Margaret March, will have
a family of my own,

08:38.999 --> 08:41.470
and, um, just be...

08:42.537 --> 08:45.139
well, happy.

08:45.639 --> 08:47.075
[Jo] And?

08:48.409 --> 08:50.245
[Meg] And nothing.

08:51.345 --> 08:53.578
- <i>Beth?</i>
- [young Beth] <i>I, Elizabeth March...</i>

08:53.580 --> 08:55.383
I, Elizabeth March...

08:57.018 --> 08:59.218
[laughs]
I don't know what to say.

08:59.220 --> 09:01.923
[Jo] Just... think about what you
want to be when you grow up.

09:03.157 --> 09:06.291
[Beth]
Well, I think this is my castle.

09:06.293 --> 09:09.364
- The attic?
- Just being here with all of you.

09:10.465 --> 09:12.397
[Jo] Okay, Beth.

09:12.399 --> 09:14.166
Yeah, that's really sweet.
We'll take it.

09:14.168 --> 09:16.435
- [giggling]
- Let's make an oath.

09:16.437 --> 09:17.469
- Okay.
- Yeah.

09:17.471 --> 09:18.941
[Jo] All right.

09:21.209 --> 09:22.311
[sighs]

09:24.479 --> 09:27.181
To always help each other
reach our castles.

09:28.048 --> 09:29.484
No matter
where they may be.

09:31.652 --> 09:32.488
[sighs]

09:34.221 --> 09:36.457
[kisses]

09:40.595 --> 09:42.064
[kisses]

09:45.332 --> 09:47.733
- [men murmuring]
- [Freddy] "Everybody gets a prize" mentality.

09:47.735 --> 09:50.269
- [Henry] My principles could be...
- [Freddy] No. Not everybody wins.

09:50.271 --> 09:53.039
Hey, excuse me!
Excuse me.

09:53.041 --> 09:54.272
- Professor Bhaer.
- Oh, dear.

09:54.274 --> 09:55.040
Hey!

09:55.042 --> 09:57.275
- It's dragon lady.
- Professor Bhaer!

09:57.277 --> 09:59.112
- Good luck with that.
- I need to talk to you.

09:59.114 --> 10:00.713
Just Jo, with the
fantasy novel, right?

10:00.715 --> 10:04.150
It's a high-fantasy
mythopoeic fable.

10:04.152 --> 10:06.352
Sorry I'm not more
familiar with that genre.

10:06.354 --> 10:09.521
Yeah, neither was your panel
of patriarchs in there.

10:09.523 --> 10:12.025
Which, you know, I might expect
from some of those hacks,

10:12.027 --> 10:13.659
but not from you.

10:13.661 --> 10:15.328
Not from someone
with your résumé.

10:15.330 --> 10:17.597
It doesn't matter.
I will find my audience,

10:17.599 --> 10:22.200
no thanks to Columbia or Hooton
Muffin or however you say it.

10:22.202 --> 10:26.271
- I'm sure you will.
- You probably didn't even understand that the protagonist

10:26.273 --> 10:29.174
- is actually a girl who dresses up as a boy.
- I didn't.

10:29.176 --> 10:31.444
And when I was growing up,
I dressed up as a boy.

10:31.446 --> 10:35.113
I was inspired by my
"authentic self," you see?

10:35.115 --> 10:39.484
I really think you would have understood
that and possibly even enjoyed it a little,

10:39.486 --> 10:42.554
had you heard more than
a measly three-minute reading

10:42.556 --> 10:45.223
in a synthetic,
almost hostile environment,

10:45.225 --> 10:49.261
where the critiques were really more
about subjective capitalistic conjecture

10:49.263 --> 10:52.198
than a chance for writers
to be discovered.

10:52.200 --> 10:54.369
I'd be happy to read
more of your novel.

10:54.835 --> 10:56.169
You would?

10:56.171 --> 10:58.404
Oh, yes! Thank you!

10:58.406 --> 11:01.207
I've been wanting anyone...
everyone... to read it.

11:01.209 --> 11:02.275
Besides my sister.

11:02.277 --> 11:04.146
Freddy, by the way.
Freddy Bhaer.

11:05.680 --> 11:09.214
Here. Contact info,
title page.

11:09.216 --> 11:10.817
E-mail would have been fine.

11:10.819 --> 11:12.418
No.

11:12.420 --> 11:16.655
You have to hold the words,
let them seep into your skin.

11:16.657 --> 11:18.757
All right.

11:18.759 --> 11:21.229
I'll be expecting your call.

11:23.764 --> 11:24.600
[sighs]

11:25.700 --> 11:28.434
[horns honking]

11:28.436 --> 11:32.137
- [machine beeps]
- <i>Hey, it's Freddy. I'm just, uh, checking in.</i>

11:32.139 --> 11:35.474
<i>I haven't heard from you. I know
that notes can be overwhelming.</i>

11:35.476 --> 11:37.175
<i>Keep your chin up.</i>

11:37.177 --> 11:39.478
- <i>Let me know when you have another draft.</i>
- [beeps]

11:39.480 --> 11:42.583
[vibrating]

11:45.152 --> 11:49.457
Josephine? Good heavens, child. It
smells like a Turkish bath in here.

11:50.457 --> 11:51.626
[sighs]

11:53.561 --> 11:57.796
If you're going to quarantine yourself
in this room for weeks on end,

11:57.798 --> 11:59.431
the least you could do
is crack a window.

11:59.433 --> 12:01.467
The least you could do
is knock.

12:01.469 --> 12:04.402
Oh, I'm your employer,
and I'm supposed to knock?

12:04.404 --> 12:06.572
How very millennial of you.

12:06.574 --> 12:08.440
Dinner's at 6:00.

12:08.442 --> 12:10.476
- I don't want her to starve
- [growls]

12:10.478 --> 12:13.346
while you escape into
your Neverwood Forest

12:13.348 --> 12:15.247
or whatever
you're scribbling about.

12:15.249 --> 12:17.382
I will do my best.

12:17.384 --> 12:19.285
Well, I sure hope
that's enough.

12:19.287 --> 12:21.355
Love you too,
Aunt March.

12:27.928 --> 12:30.231
[sighs]

12:33.868 --> 12:37.236
<i>Honey, it's Mom, just wanting
to know how your meetings went.</i>

12:37.238 --> 12:42.942
<i>So exciting. I bet they were busy fighting over
who gets to publish Concord's own Jo March.</i>

12:42.944 --> 12:44.577
[chuckles] <i>Anyway, I
know you're busy,</i>

12:44.579 --> 12:48.383
<i>but just check in and let us know when
you're coming home for Christm...</i> [beeps]

12:49.584 --> 12:52.818
[Amy] This is going to be
the worst Christmas ever.

12:52.820 --> 12:55.621
All my friends at school
get a whole pile of presents,

12:55.623 --> 12:57.593
and we get nothing.

12:59.561 --> 13:03.828
Well, we each get one gift, and
that's more than most people get.

13:03.830 --> 13:05.564
You want to know
what I asked for?

13:05.566 --> 13:08.200
Do not say a bra.

13:08.202 --> 13:09.901
New paintbrushes!

13:09.903 --> 13:11.539
[Jo] There he is again!

13:14.975 --> 13:19.280
[wind howling]

13:20.648 --> 13:22.518
[Meg] I heard he just
moved here from Europe.

13:23.585 --> 13:26.618
Maybe he was forced
to move here,

13:26.620 --> 13:29.290
after stowing away on
the Trans-Siberian railroad.

13:30.457 --> 13:33.227
Marmee said his parents
just died in a car accident.

13:33.894 --> 13:34.993
He doesn't
have any siblings,

13:34.995 --> 13:39.534
- so now he has to live with his grandfather.
- How sad.

13:43.437 --> 13:45.306
He's kind of cute, though.

13:46.441 --> 13:48.607
I mean,
I guess, for an old guy.

13:48.609 --> 13:50.809
[laughing]

13:50.811 --> 13:54.247
I don't think I could
ever live in that creepy house.

13:54.249 --> 13:55.747
Mr. Laurence is so scary.

13:55.749 --> 14:00.019
Oh, maybe Mr. Laurence
isn't his grandfather.

14:00.021 --> 14:02.288
He's the new kid's
vampire mentor,

14:02.290 --> 14:05.290
and he's trying to tame
his ravishing appetite.

14:05.292 --> 14:08.426
- Wait, that is really good.
- [chuckles]

14:08.428 --> 14:09.728
We should do something
nice for them.

14:09.730 --> 14:11.766
- Maybe we could bake them something.
- [Amy] Yes!

14:14.002 --> 14:15.734
[gasps]

14:15.736 --> 14:20.673
[on radio]
<i>♪ Angels we have heard on high ♪</i>

14:20.675 --> 14:22.275
Ooh.

14:22.277 --> 14:24.843
Amy, let's wait till
everyone gets here, okay?

14:24.845 --> 14:26.344
But I'm starving!

14:26.346 --> 14:29.015
You continue to use
that word incorrectly.

14:29.017 --> 14:31.383
- You know what I mean.
- Actually, I don't.

14:31.385 --> 14:32.550
- Shut up, Jo.
- [Marmee] Good morning!

14:32.552 --> 14:35.320
Oh, it smells like Christmas
in here.

14:35.322 --> 14:36.822
- You're back!
- How was the shelter?

14:36.824 --> 14:38.991
- [Marmee] Well...
- There were so many people there,

14:38.993 --> 14:41.327
we didn't have enough
food for everyone.

14:41.329 --> 14:43.996
See Amy? Those
people <i>are</i> starving.

14:43.998 --> 14:46.899
But not if
they like cupcakes.

14:46.901 --> 14:49.334
- Oh!
- I'll grab my costumes.

14:49.336 --> 14:51.036
We can do
the nativity musical!

14:51.038 --> 14:54.842
Oh! No, no, no, no, no.
Not the cupcakes!

14:56.043 --> 14:58.444
Can we just be
a normal family

14:58.446 --> 15:01.546
and eat breakfast
and open presents at home?

15:01.548 --> 15:03.518
- [knocks]
- I'll get that.

15:04.951 --> 15:07.053
- Oh, hi.
- [Meg] Hi.

15:07.055 --> 15:08.688
- Hey, hi.
- Hi.

15:08.690 --> 15:09.954
- Oh!
- I think this one's yours.

15:09.956 --> 15:11.357
Yeah.

15:11.359 --> 15:12.992
- Thank you so much.
- There you go.

15:12.994 --> 15:14.559
Fat ol' Goob
is always running away.

15:14.561 --> 15:17.096
- Yeah.
- Dove? Where are you?

15:17.098 --> 15:18.930
Dove? I thought
you called him Goob.

15:18.932 --> 15:20.833
Oh, I'm Dove.
I mean, I'm Meg.

15:20.835 --> 15:23.468
But my family...
That's what they call me.

15:23.470 --> 15:25.670
I'm John Brooke. I live next
door with the Laurences.

15:25.672 --> 15:27.906
- Oh.
- You don't look like a Laurence.

15:27.908 --> 15:31.711
- This is my sister, Jo.
- Yeah, I'm just a family friend of the Laurences.

15:31.713 --> 15:36.848
Mr. Laurence hired me to tutor his
grandson. Math, music and whatever else.

15:36.850 --> 15:39.852
- That's nice.
- So the new kid has a manny.

15:39.854 --> 15:41.853
Nope. Just a tutor.

15:41.855 --> 15:43.421
Right. Okay, yeah.

15:43.423 --> 15:45.524
Well, uh, we have to go
help some poor people.

15:45.526 --> 15:47.126
- Oh.
- So we'll catch you later.

15:47.128 --> 15:48.093
Merry Christmas.

15:48.095 --> 15:49.962
- Mm, bye!
- Merry Christmas.

15:49.964 --> 15:52.964
- [man] <i>Goob, buddy. Get off the computer.</i>
- [Meg] Oops, sorry, Dad.

15:52.966 --> 15:54.900
- <i>Rascal.</i>
- [meows]

15:54.902 --> 15:58.136
- Come here, Goob.
- <i>What do you got for me, Amy?</i>

15:58.138 --> 16:01.506
Okay. This one
is Marmee's favorite.

16:01.508 --> 16:04.443
- <i>Wow.</i>
- She says it's very "ethetically" pleasing.

16:04.445 --> 16:06.846
- Aesthetically.
- Aesthetically. [chuckles]

16:06.848 --> 16:10.448
<i>Well done. Amy, that's beautiful.
You're getting so good!</i>

16:10.450 --> 16:12.751
[chuckles]
Thank you.

16:12.753 --> 16:15.420
- Did I show you this one?
- No. No, no, no. Your time is up!

16:15.422 --> 16:16.421
- Jo.
- No.

16:16.423 --> 16:17.589
Come on!
Time is up!

16:17.591 --> 16:18.958
- Move.
- <i>Hey, you guys.</i>

16:18.960 --> 16:20.458
Thank you.

16:20.460 --> 16:22.127
Hi, Dad.
Okay, really quick question.

16:22.129 --> 16:26.131
Uh, when you first cut into a
liver, is the blood that seeps out,

16:26.133 --> 16:28.467
is it more crimson or maroon?

16:28.469 --> 16:30.535
<i>Writing a murder mystery,
are we?</i>

16:30.537 --> 16:34.939
- No, it's a post-apocalyptic zombie thriller.
- <i>Whoa.</i>

16:34.941 --> 16:38.777
<i>Uh, crimson, I would say.
But I only operate on humans.</i>

16:38.779 --> 16:41.947
- <i>So I don't really know about zombie blood.</i>
- Okay. Thank you.

16:41.949 --> 16:44.650
<i>All right, listen up, girls.
I only have a minute left.</i>

16:44.652 --> 16:47.051
<i>Jo, I'm going to put you
in charge of the club this year.</i>

16:47.053 --> 16:48.487
<i>So here's your marching orders.</i>

16:48.489 --> 16:50.823
[clears throat]

16:50.825 --> 16:54.193
<i>Your first assignment of the year will
be to write your grievances every week</i>

16:54.195 --> 16:56.761
<i>and come up with a plan
as to how to fix them.</i>

16:56.763 --> 17:00.735
<i>That way, you can be strong,
kind, independent little women</i>

17:01.469 --> 17:02.535
<i>like your mother.</i>

17:02.537 --> 17:05.936
- <i>Is that clear?</i>
- Sir, yes, sir!

17:05.939 --> 17:07.842
<i>Good. At ease, soldiers.</i>

17:09.175 --> 17:10.376
<i>I love you guys so much.</i>

17:10.377 --> 17:13.511
- <i>Hey, where's my beautiful Marmee?</i>
- Marmee!

17:13.512 --> 17:16.682
- <i>I need to see her one more time.</i>
- Hi.

17:16.684 --> 17:19.684
<i>Ah, there she is.
Hi, Marmee.</i>

17:19.685 --> 17:22.619
- <i>I love you so much.</i>
- [girls] Love you, Dad!

17:22.622 --> 17:24.790
<i>Merry Christmas, you guys.
I miss you so much.</i>

17:24.791 --> 17:27.460
<i>I'll think about you every day.
I promise.</i>

17:27.462 --> 17:29.094
[all]
Merry Christmas, Dad!

17:29.096 --> 17:31.864
- <i>Take care of your mom. I love you.</i>
- [Meg] Always.

17:31.866 --> 17:32.734
<i>Bye.</i>

17:38.939 --> 17:41.008
[all sigh]

17:44.544 --> 17:49.514
<i>Fifteen! Sixteen! Seventeen!</i>

17:49.516 --> 17:51.183
Say it with me, ladies!

17:51.185 --> 17:56.821
[all]
Eighteen! Nineteen! Twenty!

17:56.823 --> 18:00.494
All right. [blows whistle]
Fall in, soldiers!

18:02.964 --> 18:05.530
As Staff Sergeant
of the Pickwick Club,

18:05.532 --> 18:08.733
I request a read of the earthly
grievances of each of our members

18:08.735 --> 18:10.839
as requested
by our commander-in-chief.

18:14.574 --> 18:17.009
- Staff Sergeant Snodgrass.
- [clears throat]

18:17.011 --> 18:20.512
Your clothes and notebooks are everywhere
and when asked to clean it up,

18:20.514 --> 18:23.048
you launched an airborne Cabbage
Patch at Private Winkle's head!

18:23.050 --> 18:24.849
You're lucky
that you missed.

18:24.851 --> 18:27.086
With all due respect,
who's the lucky one?

18:27.088 --> 18:30.591
- Soldier...
- Apologies, Private. Duly noted.

18:32.859 --> 18:35.793
- [clears throat]
- Corporal Tupman.

18:35.795 --> 18:38.630
Though we love
your feline companion,

18:38.632 --> 18:41.799
we request that you fulfill
your kitty litter duties

18:41.801 --> 18:46.004
and pick up the litter box since the stench
is considered to be highly offensive.

18:46.006 --> 18:47.508
Can do, sir.

18:49.810 --> 18:55.813
Private Winkle. It has been reported
that on multiple occasions,

18:55.815 --> 18:58.951
you have stolen toilet paper
out of the latrine,

18:58.953 --> 19:02.053
with the express purpose
of stuffing your shirt.

19:02.055 --> 19:03.155
- [giggles]
- You are so mean!

19:03.157 --> 19:05.057
On the contrary.

19:05.059 --> 19:09.294
We wish only to help you enjoy
your youthful freedom,

19:09.296 --> 19:14.332
for you will soon come to know the cumbersome
and unwieldy nature of a full chest.

19:14.334 --> 19:16.702
- Like you would know.
- Private Winkle!

19:16.704 --> 19:18.169
[sighs, clears throat]

19:18.171 --> 19:20.271
General Pickwick!

19:20.273 --> 19:23.876
It has been noted that you have
not visited the shelter all week

19:23.878 --> 19:27.245
because of frequent flirtations
with the manny.

19:27.247 --> 19:29.280
So you must go twice
next week.

19:29.282 --> 19:30.886
Sir, yes, sir.

19:33.721 --> 19:38.123
- [Aunt March] Josephine, what on earth is going on here?
- [dog whining]

19:38.125 --> 19:42.828
Wha... Sorry. I'm... I'm just, uh... trying
to lay everything out, see everything.

19:42.830 --> 19:44.629
I'm not talking about
your little story.

19:44.631 --> 19:48.200
I'm talking about the fact that
Katinka's water bowl is bone dry,

19:48.202 --> 19:49.335
and she pooped
in the entryway.

19:49.337 --> 19:53.038
- Serious? I just took her out.
- When? Last Christmas?

19:53.040 --> 19:57.976
- What am I paying you for?
- I'm sorry my life doesn't revolve around your dog.

19:57.978 --> 20:01.012
Well, what does it revolve
around, exactly? Hmm?

20:01.014 --> 20:05.020
Trolls? Dragons?
Cross-dressing pirates?

20:06.853 --> 20:09.221
I don't mean
to hurt your feelings.

20:09.223 --> 20:11.255
I'm just worried
about you is all.

20:11.257 --> 20:15.194
Is this really the life you want?
The life of... insecurity?

20:15.196 --> 20:16.761
Yes.

20:16.763 --> 20:19.164
What if the professor
doesn't like this version

20:19.166 --> 20:20.098
or the next?

20:20.100 --> 20:22.734
- He will.
- I hate to see you working so hard

20:22.736 --> 20:24.703
when it could all
come to nothing.

20:24.705 --> 20:27.639
There's no shame
in changing your mind.

20:27.641 --> 20:30.709
You're still...
youngish.

20:30.711 --> 20:34.178
It's not too late to pursue something
with a little more promise in it.

20:34.180 --> 20:38.049
I know it doesn't look
like much right now,

20:38.051 --> 20:40.251
but you are going to be sorry
you ever doubted me.

20:40.253 --> 20:41.990
I certainly hope so.

20:45.392 --> 20:47.628
Just think about a
plan "B." [kisses]

20:56.771 --> 20:59.905
- I knew it. You hate the new beginning.
- No.

20:59.907 --> 21:02.875
I liked it.
A lot, actually.

21:02.877 --> 21:05.180
But then I've always been a
fan of <i>A Wrinkle in Time.</i>

21:06.379 --> 21:09.848
I am trying to get
inspired by the greats.

21:09.850 --> 21:11.817
Isn't that what artists do?

21:11.819 --> 21:13.018
Yes.

21:13.020 --> 21:15.154
And then they tell
their own stories.

21:15.156 --> 21:17.955
- Was it at least better than the last time you read it?
- It was.

21:17.957 --> 21:19.660
But...

21:20.160 --> 21:22.895
Am I a hopeless case?

21:22.897 --> 21:26.098
Please just tell me now.
Save me the heartache.

21:26.100 --> 21:28.901
You know, there are
other things I could do.

21:28.903 --> 21:31.436
I do have
marketable skills.

21:31.438 --> 21:34.306
I could be a nanny
till the day I croak.

21:34.308 --> 21:39.778
I love books. I-I should be
an old spinster librarian

21:39.780 --> 21:42.815
who reads saucy romance
novels under her desk.

21:42.817 --> 21:44.051
I'm sure you'll
find time for both.

21:45.218 --> 21:46.085
You are not helping!

21:46.087 --> 21:49.954
I'm not your therapist.
I'm your editor.

21:49.956 --> 21:51.824
I'm not going to pity an artist
for taking their stripes.

21:51.826 --> 21:55.094
You signed up for this struggle the
moment you called yourself a writer.

21:55.096 --> 21:58.030
I have a feeling you'd
be bored with anything less.

21:58.032 --> 22:02.334
[sighs] You're good, Jo.
You're a good writer.

22:02.336 --> 22:05.771
But now that I've gotten
to know you, as a person,

22:05.773 --> 22:08.072
you are far more interesting
than what you write.

22:08.074 --> 22:11.011
I want to be reading...
more of this.

22:13.214 --> 22:14.480
More of you.

22:14.482 --> 22:16.084
Me?

22:16.817 --> 22:19.417
I am not
interesting!

22:19.419 --> 22:20.586
Hell,
I'm 29 years old.

22:20.588 --> 22:23.888
And I live alone in Queens while
I work for my great aunt.

22:23.890 --> 22:25.257
I still haven't been to Europe.

22:25.259 --> 22:27.859
I haven't been marooned
on a desert island.

22:27.861 --> 22:30.796
I haven't been falsely
accused of murder.

22:30.798 --> 22:32.865
I haven't even been
a victim of identify theft!

22:32.867 --> 22:36.801
If... If my younger self
could see me now,

22:36.803 --> 22:41.875
she'd straight up join a nunnery because
at least then her life would have purpose.

22:43.144 --> 22:47.011
Actually,
that is not a bad idea.

22:47.013 --> 22:49.147
Do nuns take old people
like me?

22:49.149 --> 22:50.317
See? More of this.

22:52.253 --> 22:53.286
Where are you going?

22:53.288 --> 22:56.053
Thanks to you, I have a
whole new draft to start.

22:56.055 --> 22:59.424
We could talk about something else. It
doesn't always have to be about your work.

22:59.426 --> 23:01.059
I don't have time
to sit and chat.

23:01.061 --> 23:03.828
If my muse
isn't going to visit me,

23:03.830 --> 23:08.802
- I am going to find her and knock her dumb door down.
- [ladder rattles]

23:09.403 --> 23:11.537
Maybe I can help.

23:11.539 --> 23:13.405
- ['50s rock]
- [Amy] You guys...

23:13.407 --> 23:15.339
My nose won't stop growing!

23:15.341 --> 23:18.810
- I need a nose job.
- Take that ridiculous thing off.

23:18.812 --> 23:21.879
You don't know what it's like to have
everyone else make fun of your nose.

23:21.881 --> 23:26.151
What is it gonna be like when you cut off
your circulation and your nose falls off?

23:26.153 --> 23:28.419
- You'd look like Voldemort.
- [Jo] Oh! That would be awesome.

23:28.421 --> 23:32.124
- [chuckles]
- Why can't I go to the New Year's Eve party?

23:32.126 --> 23:34.158
You can go to all the parties
you want when you're older.

23:34.160 --> 23:38.096
For now, you can stay home and watch
the ball drop with Marmee and Beth.

23:38.098 --> 23:41.332
- Does that sound like any fun to you?
- Yes.

23:41.334 --> 23:43.100
It's not.
I'm the worst.

23:43.102 --> 23:44.903
I always fall asleep
before midnight.

23:44.905 --> 23:49.407
Yeah! You see what I mean?
Beth is so boring!

23:49.409 --> 23:52.376
And I could care less
about watching a ball drop.

23:52.378 --> 23:54.546
- [Beth] Couldn't care less.
- What's the difference?

23:54.548 --> 23:58.416
Well, if you could care less, that means you
care a little bit about the ball dropping.

23:58.418 --> 24:01.319
- I don't.
- Okay, look. I think you're lucky.

24:01.321 --> 24:04.056
I would rather pass a kidney stone
than go to this freakin' party.

24:04.058 --> 24:06.023
- You have to come with me. You promised.
- I'll go!

24:06.025 --> 24:08.527
[all]
You're too young!

24:08.529 --> 24:12.231
Can I at least
pick out your outfit?

24:12.233 --> 24:13.866
No, I'm wearing this.

24:13.868 --> 24:15.934
[Amy scoffs]
You'll never get a boyfriend.

24:15.936 --> 24:17.935
- That's the plan.
- [hissing]

24:17.937 --> 24:21.943
- I don't want a boyfriend. Boys are gross. I...
- What's that smell?

24:22.509 --> 24:23.908
[gasps]
Jo!

24:23.910 --> 24:27.613
- Are you kidding me?
- I'm sorry! You should have never let me do this!

24:27.615 --> 24:31.082
- Meg, Meg, Meg.
- [Beth] Say "sorry"!

24:31.084 --> 24:33.388
[Amy] You can just cover
it up with a headband.

24:36.490 --> 24:39.023
You still look
so pretty.

24:39.025 --> 24:40.524
It's not that bad,
is it?

24:40.526 --> 24:42.296
- [all] No.
- [Amy] Not at all.

24:47.400 --> 24:49.303
I don't like looking at
myself in the mirror.

24:50.404 --> 24:51.239
Me neither.

24:52.039 --> 24:53.571
You get used to it.

24:53.573 --> 24:56.575
Jo, why don't you wear one too?
You can match Meg.

24:56.577 --> 24:58.944
I'm not wearing
a stupid headband.

24:58.946 --> 25:03.915
You don't even like Sally Moffat, and
her, like, giggly little brat pack.

25:03.917 --> 25:07.051
- They're not that bad.
- They talk about the stupidest things.

25:07.053 --> 25:09.421
And her brother always
gives me the weirdest looks.

25:09.423 --> 25:12.026
Let's go get pizza instead
and say that we didn't.

25:13.694 --> 25:15.260
Jo, listen.

25:15.262 --> 25:18.131
I'm sick of being the weird
home-schooled sisters.

25:20.301 --> 25:24.302
I want to make friends and go to
parties and talk to guys our own age.

25:24.304 --> 25:26.006
Why?

25:26.540 --> 25:28.307
Because I just do!

25:28.309 --> 25:29.207
[sighs]

25:29.209 --> 25:31.879
And I really need
you to be my wing woman.

25:35.014 --> 25:38.151
[sighs] Wing woman
reporting for duty.

25:38.686 --> 25:40.219
[squeals]

25:40.221 --> 25:43.422
[hip-hop] <i>♪ It's Saturday night
And I'm feeling real good ♪</i>

25:43.424 --> 25:46.157
I am so glad you're here.

25:46.159 --> 25:50.297
I have somebody that I have been
meaning to introduce you to.

25:54.400 --> 25:56.370
You. Who are you?

25:57.603 --> 26:00.040
And who do you know here?

26:02.176 --> 26:03.477
Hi.

26:05.579 --> 26:06.979
- Sorry!
- Excuse me.

26:06.981 --> 26:09.114
[screams]

26:09.116 --> 26:13.251
- Meg. This has to go.
- Hi.

26:13.253 --> 26:16.555
And you
are coming with me.

26:16.557 --> 26:18.059
Bye.

26:18.993 --> 26:20.591
So much for
wing womaning.

26:20.593 --> 26:23.194
<i>♪ We tip 'em so big
So they serve what we wish ♪</i>

26:23.196 --> 26:25.030
<i>♪ A good night
This is what it is ♪</i>

26:25.032 --> 26:27.331
<i>♪ We just don't go out clubbing
First we cruising ♪</i>

26:27.333 --> 26:29.467
<i>♪ And my boys I call 'em up ♪</i>

26:29.469 --> 26:32.236
<i>♪ Tell 'em where we at
And what is up ♪</i>

26:32.238 --> 26:35.607
<i>♪ It's Saturday night
And I'm feeling real good ♪</i>

26:35.609 --> 26:38.710
<i>♪ Usually I be chilling
But tonight I feel like ♪</i>

26:38.712 --> 26:40.544
<i>♪ I hit the club and get loose ♪</i>

26:40.546 --> 26:43.016
<i>♪ Yeah, I feel good
And it's Saturday night ♪</i>

26:44.051 --> 26:45.384
<i>♪ Everything going smooth ♪</i>

26:45.386 --> 26:48.587
<i>♪ Gotta call my crew
'Cause tonight be the night ♪</i>

26:48.589 --> 26:51.490
<i>♪ We hit the club
And get loose ♪</i>

26:51.492 --> 26:53.127
[muffled music]

26:53.793 --> 26:55.530
- Sorry!
- Sorry.

26:56.696 --> 26:59.030
Avoiding people?

26:59.032 --> 27:00.265
- What?
- Me too.

27:00.267 --> 27:03.534
I'm only here because my grandpa
thinks I need to make friends.

27:03.536 --> 27:07.405
I guess when your grandpa thinks
you're a loner, you probably are.

27:07.407 --> 27:09.808
So you're the infamous
Laurence grandson.

27:09.810 --> 27:11.009
Infamous?

27:11.011 --> 27:15.780
Well, my theory... was that you
were an international spy,

27:15.782 --> 27:19.651
seeking refuge
in an inconspicuous town.

27:19.653 --> 27:21.055
Well, you're right.

27:21.655 --> 27:23.821
- And now you die.
- [grunts]

27:23.823 --> 27:25.459
[chuckles]

27:26.392 --> 27:28.393
I'm Jo.

27:28.395 --> 27:29.464
Laurie.

27:31.799 --> 27:33.732
Goody-goody, Meggy March.

27:33.734 --> 27:36.068
Who let you
out of the henhouse?

27:36.070 --> 27:39.404
[chanting] Drink! Drink!
Drink! Drink!

27:39.406 --> 27:41.138
Whoo!

27:41.140 --> 27:43.176
- Come on. It's not gonna kill you!
- I'll do it.

27:45.712 --> 27:47.145
You speak French?

27:47.147 --> 27:49.280
I had to.
I lived there for three years.

27:49.282 --> 27:51.715
No way. You have to
tell me all about it!

27:51.717 --> 27:54.653
I'm going to Paris
after college.

27:54.655 --> 27:56.555
I'm gonna do
all the things.

27:56.557 --> 28:00.524
It's pretty much just like anywhere else.
It's just... more French.

28:00.526 --> 28:03.395
Well, it's definitely
not as boring as here.

28:03.397 --> 28:07.732
Here's not so bad.
So far at least.

28:07.734 --> 28:09.434
I cannot wait
to leave this place.

28:09.436 --> 28:11.837
I have two years
till I go to Oxford.

28:11.839 --> 28:14.172
I'm a novelist
and a playwright.

28:14.174 --> 28:16.674
I'm going to be very
successful and very rich.

28:16.676 --> 28:19.610
Not like filthy rich
like you and your grandpa,

28:19.612 --> 28:22.646
but just rich enough that I buy a
house in Europe and bring my sisters

28:22.648 --> 28:23.882
and pay for everything.

28:23.884 --> 28:25.649
Wow, sounds like
you've got it all figured out.

28:25.651 --> 28:27.719
<i>♪ Stay in the zone
Where I'm just me, girl ♪</i>

28:27.721 --> 28:30.688
<i>♪ Super faded Sometimes
I feel Like I made it ♪</i>

28:30.690 --> 28:32.824
<i>♪ Nine clouds high
Wave good-bye ♪</i>

28:32.826 --> 28:34.893
<i>♪ Goin' to a world where
You're my girl and ♪</i>

28:34.895 --> 28:38.762
[hip-hop continues]

28:38.764 --> 28:42.733
Ferdinand doesn't want to go into the
jungle until she has both of her legs,

28:42.735 --> 28:45.770
- so she has to wait until the curse is lifted.
- Naturally.

28:45.772 --> 28:47.739
But the thing
that she doesn't know

28:47.741 --> 28:51.675
is that she actually has to get
to the edge of the jungle

28:51.677 --> 28:52.978
for the curse to be lifted!

28:52.980 --> 28:57.549
- See, so it's this whole <i>Catch-22</i> thing.
- [song changes]

28:57.551 --> 28:59.885
Wait, wait, wait.
I love this song!

28:59.887 --> 29:01.252
- Come on!
- Wait! What?

29:01.254 --> 29:04.422
<i>♪ Baby, don't fight ♪</i>

29:04.424 --> 29:06.290
<i>♪ I want to see you
Move tonight ♪</i>

29:06.292 --> 29:08.425
<i>♪ Turn out the lights ♪</i>

29:08.427 --> 29:10.694
<i>♪ Dancing is a human right ♪</i>

29:10.696 --> 29:12.731
<i>♪ Baby, don't fight ♪</i>

29:12.733 --> 29:14.732
<i>♪ I want to see you
Move tonight ♪</i>

29:14.734 --> 29:17.234
<i>♪ Turn out the lights ♪</i>

29:17.236 --> 29:19.370
<i>♪ Dancing is a human right ♪</i>

29:19.372 --> 29:21.405
